name: Wizardry II
description:
Wizards Assembly 

The ambivalence of uncommon spirits among humans. In the Third Age of Middle-Earth, it was believed wizards were human who over the time has secretly mastered the art of Lore and Art. As soon as the third age passed it was observed that the wizards do not tasted death. So, men began to see them as not just human but of Elven-kind.
